        "text": "## Debugging Capabilities Available\n\n### Session & Process Debugging\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| **session_status** | Shows session usage, time, cost, and reasoning status. Use to check model, runtime info |\n| **sessions_list** | List active sessions with filters (activeMinutes, kinds, limit) |\n| **sessions_history** | Fetch message history for any session (includeTools shows tool calls) |\n| **process** | Manage exec sessions: `list`, `poll`, `log`, `write`, `send-keys`, `submit`, `paste`, `kill` |\n| **subagents** | List, kill, or steer spawned sub-agents |\n\n### Shell & Execution\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| **exec** | Run shell commands with optional elevated permissions, PTY support, and timeouts |\n| **exec.ask** | For approval-pending commands (shows allow-once/allow-always/deny) |\n\n### Memory & State Inspection\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| **memory_search** | Semantically search MEMORY.md + memory/*.md files |\n| **memory_get** | Read specific lines from memory files |\n| **read** | Inspect any file in workspace or system |\n\n### From `~/.openclaw/state/internal.json`\n- **Plugin**: `status-skill` \u2014 provides health/status checking\n- **Workflow**: `reminder-workflow` \u2014 cron-based reminder system\n\n### OpenClaw Daemon\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway status   # Check gateway daemon\nopenclaw gateway restart # Restart if stuck\n```\n\nThe most useful for real-time debugging are `session_status`, `sessions_history` (with includeTools:true), and `process` for watching running shell sessions.",
